o' b'ossa: office of space science and applications' b'osse: oriented scintillation spectrometer experiment (on cgro)' b'ota: optical telescope assembly (on hst)' b'othb: over the horizon backscatter' b'otv: orbital transfer vehicle' b'ov: orbital vehicle' b'pam: payload assist module' b'pam-d: payload assist module, delta-class' b'pi: principal investigator' b'plss: portable life support system' b'pm: pressurized module' b'pmc: permanently manned capability' b'pmirr: pressure modulated infrared radiometer (on mars observer)' b'pmt: photomultiplier tube' b'psf: point spread function' b'psr: pulsar' b'pv: photovoltaic' b'pvo: pioneer venus orbiter' b'qso: quasi-stellar object' b'rci: rodent cage interface (for sls mission)' b'rcs: reaction control system' b'rem: rat enclosure module (for sls mission)' b'rf: radio frequency' b'rfi: radio frequency interference' b'riacs: research institute for advanced computer science' b'rms: remote manipulator system' b'rngc: revised new general catalog' b'rosat: roentgen satellite' b"rous: rodents of unusual size (i don't believe they exist)" b'rsn: real soon now' b'rtg: radioisotope thermoelectric generator' b'rtls: return to launch site (shuttle abort plan)' b'saa: south atlantic anomaly' b'saga: solar array gain augmentation (for hst)' b'sampex: solar anomalous and magnetospheric particle explorer' b'sao: smithsonian astrophysical observatory' b'sar: search and rescue' b'sar: synthetic aperture radar' b'sara: satellite pour astronomie radio amateur' b'sarex: search and rescue exercise' b'sarex: shuttle amateur radio experiment' b'sas: space activity suit' b'sas: space adaptation syndrome' b'sat: synthetic aperture telescope' b's/c: spacecraft' b'sca: shuttle carrier aircraft' b'sct: schmidt-cassegrain telescope' b'sdi: strategic defense initiative' b'sdio: strategic defense initiative organization' b'sei: space exploration initiative' b'sest: swedish eso submillimeter telescope' b'seti: search for extraterrestrial intelligence' b